Here is the job specification:

Do you want to be a valued part of the critical infrastructure that serves communities across Europe and beyond? Are you looking for a position in which you can set direction and help shape our company? If so, then you could be the newest addition to our team as Sales Manager.

About the role

With a strong knowledge of the shipping and logistics industry, you’ll be responsible for the local sales team as well as new business development. You will be an integral part of a wider Commercial team. Within the role, we need you to be a strong leader as well as be proactive in dealing with prospects, converting them to business opportunities, and ultimately into new clients.

You will be responsible for the:

Develop and implement strategic sales plans to achieve company objectives and targets;
Identify and pursue new business opportunities within the European market;
Build and maintain strong relationships with existing clients, understanding their needs and providing tailored solutions;
Responsible for Sales team of three dedicated colleagues;
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including operations, logistics, and customer service, to ensure excellent service delivery;
Conduct market research and analysis to identify market trends, competitive activities, and potential growth areas;
Prepare sales forecasts, budgets, and reports, providing regular updates to senior management;
Attend industry conferences, trade shows, and networking events to promote company services and generate leads;
Stay up to date with industry developments, regulations, and best practices in cold chain management
Requirements:

Proven track record of success in sales within the European logistics industry;
Strong understanding of the European logistics industry;
Excellent communication and negotiation skills, with the ability to build rapport and establish long-term relationships;
Demonstrated ability to work independently and as part of a team in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment;
Proficiency in English (additional European languages are a plus);
Willingness to travel within the European Continent as required
